  <h2 id="tables-responsive-rows-and-absolute-cols">Responsive - Absolute
    columns</h2>
  <p>Sometimes you need a <code>&lt;td&gt;</code> to act as a column that goes
    100% height of the table.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Add <code>.t-has-absolute-col-left</code> and/or <code>.t-absolute-col-right</code>
      to the <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code>.</li>
    <li>Add <code>.t-absolute-col-left</code> and/or <code>.t-absolute-col-right</code>
      to <code>&lt;td&gt;</code>s that will be the "absolute" column.</li>
    <li>Add <code>.t-col-sibling-both</code> to <code>&lt;td&gt;</code>s that
      have a columns on both immediate left and right.</li>
    <li>Add <code>.t-col-sibling-left</code> to <code>&lt;td&gt;</code>s that
      have a column to it's immediate left.</li>
    <li>Add <code>.t-col-sibling-right</code> to <code>&lt;td&gt;</code>s that
      have a column to it's immediate right.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bs-example">
    <div class="table-responsive-rows-and-cols">
      <table class="table table-striped">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th class="t-checkbox"></th>
            <th class="t-firstname">First Name</th>
            <th class="t-lastname">Last Name</th>
            <th class="t-phone">Phone</th>
            <th class="t-email">Email</th>
            <th class="t-online-customer">Online Customer</th>
            <th class="t-actions">Actions</th>
